The paper deals with text categorization, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The algorithm presented in the paper is based on supervised learning, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves similarity search, which is a common technique in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DS.
